So as I understand it;

5v is going to <CHIP>U7801</CHIP>, when it get's EN, it sends the 5v through <RESISTOR>R7801</RESISTOR> TO <TRANSISTOR>Q7801</TRANSISTOR> where it gets turn into 1.3v (should be 1.5 though?) and then off down <SIGNAL>PP1V5_S3RS0_FET7</SIGNAL>.
It seems like <CHIP>U7901</CHIP> is getting the current back through Pin6, this would be a feedback loop to make sure its the correct voltage maybe?
